<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-064-184 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 203 771</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Sept 4 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Computer Associates to acquire Pansophic. (Pansophic Systems)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Buckler, Grant.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Computer Associates International Inc. Computer Associates MicroProducts Div. (Acquisitions, mergers, divestments)Pansophic Systems Inc. (Acquisitions, mergers, divestments).andO;Ticker:    PNS.andO;Topic:     AcquisitionStock.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>****COMPUTER ASSOCIATES TO ACQUIRE PANSOPHIC 09/04/91 GARDEN CITY, NEW YORK,U.S.A., 1991 SEP 4 (NB) -- Computer Associates has agreed in principle toacquire all outstanding shares of fellow software developer Pansophic Systemsof Lisle, Illinois.andM;Computer Associates is to pay $16.15 per share in cash for Pansophic commonstock.andM;The deal is subject to written confirmation of financing and to the approvalof both companies' boards of directors, as well as to regulatory approvals.andO;Computer Associates said it expects to have a firm commitment on financing byFriday, September 6, when the boards of directors of both companies are tomeet.andM;If financing is not confirmed, Computer Associates said, it has agreed not toseek to acquire Pansophic at a price below $16.15 per share, or to launch aproxy contest or take any similar action.andM;A more-or-less final decision on the deal is expected Friday, said MaryKeating, a spokeswoman for Computer Associates in Toronto.andM;Computer Associates is a diversified software firm that offers products formainframes, minicomputers, and personal computers.andP;  Its personal computerproducts include the SuperCalc spreadsheet software, SuperProject projectmanagement software, and the Accpac line of accounting packages.andM;Pansophic is a large maker of applications software for a range of computerhardware, with a focus on larger systems.andM;This is the second acquisition in a month for CA, which agreed in late Augustto acquire all outstanding stock of On-Line Software International of FortLee, New Jersey.andP;  The company has grown in the past few years through theacquisition of mainframe software firms Applied Data Research and Cullinet,the PC accounting products of Bedford Software, and other purchases.andM;Though the company has not officially revealed its plans for Pansophic,Keating said CA typically absorbs acquired companies and integrates theirproduct lines with its own rather than operating them as separatesubsidiaries.andM;(Grant Buckler/19910904/Press Contact: Deborah Coughlin, Computer Associates,516-227-3300 ext. 7129, fax 516-227-3937; G. Gordon M. Large, Pansophic,708-505-6590)</TEXT></DOC>